result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 10:53 am cases called. 15CM166 & 15CM191. Defendant Robert T. Ely in court with attorney Paul Edward Zilles.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agreement stated on record by ADA Anderson.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:  No Contest to Count 1 & 2-15CM166. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in 15CM191. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS: COUNT 1 ONLY- 52 days WCJ with 52 days credit for time served. CONDITIONS on both counts-AODA and follow through,   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No Contact with Barbara Hedrick. DAAP and follow through, Terms of Agent. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Appeal Rights Given.

NOT PUT OF RECORD: Attorney Paul Edward Zilles in court.  Scott Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Zilles states matters can be set for plea/sentencing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 21, 2015 at 10:30 am.
15CM166 & 15CM191 Cases called @ 12:12 p.m. Defendant Robert T. Ely in court, in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. The court will reschedule with Atty Zilles.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
